FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,FHe said Labour is "lacking a project"
OL,7,Fand was "playing with the future of
OL,8,Fthe country" in a 5,700-word essay
OL,9,Fwhich was published on Tuesday.
OL,11,FHe highlighted a number of areas where
OL,12,Fhe disagreed with the government since
OL,13,Fit came into office in July 2024.
OL,15,FThe Labour leader, who left office in
OL,16,F2007, said Labour had held back
OL,17,Fbusiness and growth since it won the
OL,18,Felection.
OL,26,@nD@SOUnD@eO]oD@IOUpD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,FBlair referenced the increase in
OL,7,Femployers' national insurance, the
OL,8,Fworkers' rights bill and the rise in
OL,9,Fminimum wage.
OL,11,FHe was also critical of the
OL,12,Fgovernment's spending on welfare and
OL,13,Fcalled for the triple lock on pensions
OL,14,Fto be reformed.
OL,16,FThe former prime minister said: "The
OL,17,FLabour Party is playing with fire; or,
OL,18,Fmore accurately, with its future, and
OL,19,Fthat of the country."
OL,26,@xD@aOU{D@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,FHe went on: "The government's
OL,7,Fprincipal problem isn't Keir's
OL,8,Fpersonality. Or a failure to
OL,9,Fcommunicate 'our achievements'. Or a
OL,10,Fneed to assert more strongly Labour's
OL,11,F'values'.
OL,13,F"It is because we don't have a worked
OL,14,Fout, coherent plan for the country in
OL,15,Fa fast-changing world and are in the
OL,16,Fwrong political position from which we
OL,17,Fcan devise one and win a second term.
OL,26,@nD@MOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"The government is governing from an
OL,7,Fessentially traditional Labour 'soft
OL,8,Fleft' position, parked firmly in the
OL,9,Fparty's comfort zone."
OL,11,FHe said the government should not have
OL,12,Fstopped the US from using its RAF
OL,13,Fbases during the attacks on Iran.
OL,15,FBlair also said the government should
OL,16,Fdo "whatever it takes" to stop the
OL,17,Fsmall boats crisis and laid out a 10-
OL,18,Fpoint plan for the future of
OL,19,Fgovernment.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@VO]xD@DOUxD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
