PN,31309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"The government took with it into
OL,7,Fpower commitments which meant that
OL,8,Fthere was an inevitable gap between
OL,9,Fthe government rhetoric around growth
OL,10,Fand the impact of these commitments on
OL,11,Fwhat the business community needed to
OL,12,Frestore the so-called animal spirits
OL,13,Fand get the private sector moving," he
OL,14,Fsaid.
OL,16,FHe continued: "The prime minister and
OL,17,Fthe chancellor should have said right
OL,18,Fat the outset: these are commitments
OL,19,Fwhich economic circumstances have
OL,20,Frendered unwise to proceed with. The
OL,21,Fpriority is growth.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@cO]xD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"That comes with a vibrant private
OL,7,Fsector which has suffered years of
OL,8,Feconomic instability, and we are going
OL,9,Fto go all-out for making business feel
OL,10,Frespected and supported.
OL,12,F"Dropping the commitments would have
OL,13,Fbeen painful but bearable because the
OL,14,Fgovernment would have started with
OL,15,Freal goodwill from business.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"But we didn't, and to compound the
OL,7,Fproblem, we chose a rise in national
OL,8,Finsurance, not VAT, to plug the fiscal
OL,9,Fgap in the first Budget. Either tax
OL,10,Fincrease would have been unpopular.
OL,11,FOnly one undermined business
OL,12,Fconfidence.
OL,14,F"Then, in the last Budget, it appeared
OL,15,Fas if we were increasing tax to pay
OL,16,Ffor additional welfare spending, when
OL,17,Fthe public already thinks welfare
OL,18,Fbills are too high.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"Taken together, these measures have
OL,7,Fgiven headwinds, not tailwinds, to
OL,8,FBritish business, despite the
OL,9,Fmacroeconomic gains for which the
OL,10,Fchancellor is rightly praised.
OL,12,F"At a minimum, the government should
OL,13,Ftry to limit the effect of the changes
OL,14,Fmade and, as we have argued
OL,15,Fconsistently, remove those parts of
OL,16,Fthe net-zero agenda which prioritise
OL,17,Fclean energy over cheaper energy; and
OL,18,Ffrom now on make sure the actions
OL,19,Fmatch the words on growth."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU{D@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
