OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,FDespite backing Remain in the Brexit
OL,7,Freferendum, and later a second vote,
OL,8,FBlair cautioned against a push to
OL,9,Frejoin the European Union.
OL,11,FInstead, he suggested both should work
OL,12,Fon areas of shared interest, including
OL,13,Fdefence and energy.
OL,15,F"The truth is that Britain has lost
OL,16,Ffrom Brexit. But so has Europe," he
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,26,@wD@AOUxD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1779894668
OL,3,C'Labour lacks coherent plan' says Tony
OL,4,CBlair in essay on government failings
OL,6,F"We're both weaker without the other.
OL,7,FBut we can't go back to cohabitation
OL,8,Funless on a basis which enhances our
OL,9,Fcapabilities, economic and political,
OL,10,Fand does not undermine them ` and that
OL,11,Fgoes for both of us."
OL,13,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,14,Four political experts are across all
OL,15,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,16,Fto the latest episode below...
